Create Seurat Object - all samples

suppressMessages(library(SingleCellExperiment))
suppressMessages(library(Seurat))
suppressMessages(library(ggplot2))
sce <- readRDS("/mnt/nmorais-nfs/marta/pB_joana/pC_data/sce_all-samples-after-qc.rds")
norm_mat <- (2**assays(sce)$logcounts)-1
## Warning in asMethod(object): sparse->dense coercion: allocating vector of size
## 5.1 GiB
ln_mat <- log(norm_mat + 1)
ln_mat[1:5]
## [1] 0.000000 1.111906 0.000000 1.111906 0.000000
srt <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = ln_mat, min.cells = 0, min.features = 0)

## unique

srt
## An object of class Seurat 
## 16864 features across 40956 samples within 1 assay 
## Active assay: RNA (16864 features, 0 variable features)
srt <- FindVariableFeatures(srt, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 3000)
# Identify the 20 most highly variable genes
top20 <- head(VariableFeatures(srt), 20)

# plot variable features with and without labels
plot1 <- VariableFeaturePlot(srt)
plot2 <- LabelPoints(plot = plot1, points = top20, repel = TRUE)
## When using repel, set xnudge and ynudge to 0 for optimal results
plot2

all.genes <- rownames(srt)
srt <- ScaleData(srt, features = all.genes)
## Centering and scaling data matrix
srt <- RunPCA(srt, features = VariableFeatures(object = srt), npcs = 50)
